# Exercise:  Refer to Lial Section 14.1 Example 2. Duplicate the results showing plots of the function and derivatives.

figure()
p=poly1d([3,-4,-12,0,2])

print ('\nFourth Degree Polynomial') 
print p
print ('\nFirst Derivative')

g= p.deriv(m=1) # First derivative with m=1.
print g
print ('\nSecond Derivative')

q= p.deriv(m=2) # Second derivative with m=2.
print q

x=linspace(-2,3,101)
y=p(x)
yg=g(x) # 
These statements define points for plotting.
yq=q(x)
y0=0*x # This statement defines the y axis for plotting.

